println("  W3 epinephrine pH 8.5 degradation: 30% loss @ 30min, 100% @ 2 weeks (Sciencedirect 1990)")
println("     -> BILAYER PHYSICAL SEPARATION MANDATORY (epi in acidic bottom only, never in top)")
println("     -> rules OUT N7-B without polymer barrier; rules IN N7-A (2 SKUs) and N7-C (microcap)")
println("  W4 lid amide hydrolysis @ pH 8.5: Powell 1987 t_1/2 ~ months @ RT")
println("     -> shelf-life fine if alkaline contact <hours total over 24mo")
println("     -> N7-B (continuous alkaline contact) needs polymer barrier or refrigeration")
println("  W5 carbonate buffer capacity: skin secretes lactate (acid mantle); pH neutralizes within min")
println("     -> N7-A wait-time critical (3-5min before top apply); N7-C needs HIGH carbonate (20%+ w/w)")
println("  W6 regulatory novelty: pH-gradient bilayer = no FDA-approved precedent in topical anesthetic")
println("     buffered lid INJECTION (NaHCO3) is well-precedented; transdermal pH gradient = NEW")
println("     -> 505(b)(2) feasible w/ RLD = LMX-5 / Pliaglis (lid base), pH shift = formulation novelty")
